&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TENBURY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; COMMUNITY HOSPITAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;REGISTERED NURSE or REGISTERED NURSING ASSOCIATE &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 hours per week – 11.5 hours shifts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;T&lt;/span&gt;enbury Hospital is a small friendly community hospital supporting our local population through a dedicated team of staff.  We provide intermediate care, rehabilitation and palliative care and have a Minor injury unit, an outpatient department, x-ray facilities and have the local Neighborhood team based on site.  We take patients from acute settings and from home and hospitals outside of the area.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust actively supports staff education and development. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require an innovative, enthusiastic and motivated individual to work in our team. You will be supported to plan, implement, evaluate and take responsibility for the nursing care of the ward patients daily. You will have a flexible approach to working and be willing to participate in the development of the wards. You should have a minimum qualification of registered nursing associate. This post would suit a newly qualified RNA with post registration nursing experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal enquiries welcomed by Sharon Price, Ward Manager on 01584 81064.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
